
[1]apostate

   APOS'TATE, n. [Gr.]

   One who has forsaken the church, sect or profession to which he before
   adhered. In its original sense, applied to one who has abandoned his
   religion; but correctly applied also to one who abandons a political or
   other party.

                      APOS'TATE, a. False; traitorous.
